!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

mighty /ˈmaɪtɪ/

(mightier,mightiest) 

1. ADJ Mighty is used to describe something that is very large or powerful. 强大的 [文学性] 

例： There was a flash and a mighty bang. 一道闪光伴随着一声轰然巨响。 

2. ADV Mighty is used in front of adjectives and adverbs to emphasize the quality that they are describing. 非常 [美国英语] [非正式] [ADV adj/adv] 

例： It's something you'll be mighty proud of. 这是个你会非常骄傲的事。 

3.  →  see also high-and-mighty

